Sure, here are some example sentences using the Serbian word "ponos" in different forms and positions, with translations in English in parentheses:

1. Moj *ponos* me je sprečio da prihvatim njegovu pomoć. (My pride prevented me from accepting his help.)
2. On je ispunjen *ponosom* kada vidi svoje uspehe. (He is filled with pride when he sees his accomplishments.)
3. *Ponosan* sam na svoje poreklo i svoju kulturu. (I am proud of my heritage and my culture.)
4. Ona je *ponosna* majka koja voli svoju decu iznad svega. (She is a proud mother who loves her children above all.)
5. Njihov *ponos* je sprečio da priznaju svoju grešku. (Their pride prevented them from admitting their mistake.)
6. *Ponosno* je nosio svoj dres reprezentacije na utakmici. (He proudly wore his national team jersey at the game.)
7. Svi u selu su *ponosni* na svoju tradiciju i običaje. (Everyone in the village is proud of their traditions and customs.)
8. Njen *ponos* ju je naterao da raskine sa njim. (Her pride made her break up with him.)
9. Kao *ponosna* osoba, ona nije tražila nikakvu pomoć. (As a proud person, she did not ask for any help.)
10. On nije pokazivao *ponos* kada je izgubio utakmicu. (He did not show any pride when he lost the game.)

I hope these examples are helpful!